input: Anne is nice. Anne is young. Bob is furry. Bob is quiet. Bob is rough. Bob is not white. Bob is not young. Gary is furry. Gary is not quiet. Gary is young. Harry is young. If something is quiet and young then it is rough. If Harry is furry then Harry is not rough. If something is young then it is furry. Young, quiet things are round. If Harry is round then Harry is nice. All nice things are white. If Harry is not rough then Harry is round. Question: Harry is white.?
output:
universe u

constant obj : Type u

constant Anne : obj
constant Bob : obj
constant Gary : obj
constant Harry : obj

constant Nice : obj → Prop
constant Young : obj → Prop
constant Furry : obj → Prop
constant Quiet : obj → Prop
constant Rough : obj → Prop
constant White : obj → Prop
constant Round : obj → Prop

axiom T1 : Nice Anne
axiom T2 : Young Anne
axiom T3 : Furry Bob
axiom T4 : Quiet Bob
axiom T5 : Rough Bob
axiom T6 : ¬ White Bob
axiom T7 : ¬ Young Bob
axiom T8 : Furry Gary
axiom T9 : ¬ Quiet Gary
axiom T10 : Young Gary
axiom T11 : Young Harry

axiom R1 : ∀ x : obj, Quiet x ∧ Young x → Rough x
axiom R2 : Furry Harry → ¬ Rough Harry
axiom R3 : ∀ x : obj, Young x → Furry x
axiom R4 : ∀ x : obj, Young x ∧ Quiet x → Round x
axiom R5 : Round Harry → Nice Harry
axiom R6 : ∀ x : obj, Nice x → White x
axiom R7 : ¬ Rough Harry → Round Harry

theorem harry_is_white : White Harry :=
begin
  apply R6,
  apply R5,
  apply R7,
  apply R2,
  apply R3,
  exact T11,
end

-- The answer is True
